SENATE RESOLUTION 17
By Lamar
A RESOLUTION to honor Carlissa A. Shaw in celebration of
Women's Day on the Hill.
WHEREAS, Women's Day on the Hill is a time to honor the achievements of those
Tennessee women who have paved the way for every person to have the opportunity to pursue
the American dream; and
WHEREAS, the Volunteer State is proud to be the home of the awe-inspiring Carlissa A.
Shaw, a native of Memphis who has served as an attorney, advocate, and activist for decades;
she is the founder of The CASE FIRM, co-founder of Esquire Investments, and co-founder of
the Memphis Women's Expo, which seeks to inspire, empower, and connect women from
diverse backgrounds; and
WHEREAS, she has served as co-chair of the Civilian Law Enforcement Review Board
and was recruited by the Tennessee Democratic Party to co-chair the committee tasked with
reorganizing the Shelby County Democratic Party; her other roles have included Assistant
County Attorney for Shelby County and Chief Policy Advisor to the Shelby County
Environmental Court; and
WHEREAS, Carlissa Shaw has further served her profession and community as
President of the Ben F. Jones Chapter of the National Bar Association and a member of various
boards, including those of WILLOW (Women In Leadership Leaning On Wisdom), Memphis For
All, and Hospitality Hub, a nonprofit dedicated to ending homelessness; and
WHEREAS, in saluting Ms. Shaw on this special occasion, let us remember that when
women succeed, America succeeds, as does Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby honor and commend
